      • LoadURLParams

        public LoadURLParams(java.lang.String url,
                     java.lang.String postData)
        Constructs a new LoadURLParams instance.
        Parameters:
        url - represents URL of the resource that will be loaded. Cannot be null.
        postData - a string that represents POST data in the key=value&key=value... format. The supported content type of the POST data is application/x-www-form-urlencoded.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when when url is null or empty.
